column25:
our company concerns about food safety and the fact that many processed foods are made from genetically modified products. Organically grown foods mean that these organic foods have been grown on land that is absent of any chemicals for a minimum of 3 years. The crops are grown without the use of pesticides or any chemicals whatsoever. Organic foods are processed and packaged without the use of artificial preservatives, colorings, irradiation or any other additives.
we produce all kind of organic fresh fruits and vegetables.
column26:
There are numerous benefits to both eating organic foods, and to organic gardening. we personally believe that a huge benefit comes from a renewed relationship with nature. It starts with an "I won"t poison you, you won"t poison me" attitude, and ends with "I"ll nurture and respect you, you nurture and respect me." 

 Gardening is just plain good for the soul. 

so our target for all the people to be on the safe  side.
eating organic it means eating healthy food.

cause our business secret is based on the international exchange rates from us dollars to pounds,it means there is a huge benefits from the cost of production in lebanon for the fresh fruits and vegetables to be delivered to london.
we can explain it , like for an exemple 1$usd cost of production could be sale at 5 pound in the UK.
this make a huge difference between the cost of prodction and the sale prices.
column29:
in fact there is no competitor in our private line of production cause we produce a specific kind of organic fresh fruits and vegetables to be delivered on daily to heathrow airport in london by the british airways and MEA.
after our study of the lebanese market and  companies , we found that there is no competitor befor we start our line of production who is working on export organic to the UK.from beirut to london.

that is an advantage for us to build the first one billion of usd in easy way.
this is not just a number we can prove it.
column30:
The pros in "going organic" is that organic food is free from artificial chemicals, pesticides, antibiotics, growth-promoters and fertilizers. It is produced using environmentally friendly methods and is free from genetically modified ingredients .
       Organic foods according to some studies show that they have more vitamins and beneficial trace elements than conventionally grown food and so may be more nutritious .

 Who knows what will be considered healthy eating in the future At this point, organic foods seem to be beneficial.

column25: My company will specialize in buying top selling video game licenses and dub the score/script into the Arabic language. Furthermore, a website with an online store will be created in order to host my products and a complete online marketing strategy will ensure visibility and increase sales. In the future the company will develop Arabic video games in house and contribute in creating local job opportunities.
column26:
My target audience will be local and regional Arabs from different age group that have access to the internet and would be interested in my products. 49% of the online users in MENA region are under twenty five years of age.
33% of the online users in the MENA region are between 26 and 35 years of age.
The rest of the online users (18%) in the MENA region are over 35 years of age.
It is important to note that the purchasing power is divided between these three groups. We will have a variety in our products that would appeal to large chunk of MENA online users.
column27: Since the nature of our product will appeal to Arabs, the major geographical target market would be the MENA region. Nevertheless, expatriates all over the globe could purchase our products through an easy 3 step online checkout system. In the beginning it is important to target the GCC countries because they have the largest percentage of purchasing power between all the regional countries.
column28: according to the internet world stats and the MADAR research, 34 million internet users in the Middle East, 17.5 million users in the GCC-Levant region, with 920% growth from year 2000 to 2007. the size of the market would be at a minimum of 34 million dollars.
column29: My competitors in the Middle East would be established video game resellers, video game developers and international distributors. Already a social network base online video game called trivian.ae is being marketed extensively all over the net and is ranking extremely high in terms of visibility and online user registration. As long as the internet penetration is growing in the MENA region, I would expect a equal growth of competitors in the next 5 years.
column30: My product would consist of popular video games that are being dubbed into an Arabic and this alone is a new concept that would be Attractive to my target audience. Furthermore, in order to appeal to a larger audience, i will get popular Arab sports anchors and celebrities to dub the scripts and characters. My products would bring a customized video gaming experience that is totally adapted to an Arab audience. My products would be supported by online forums where people can join and connect, all in Arabic. My products will be high in quality at affordable prices. My products would be accessible to all age groups and purchased at all major retail stores and/or online.
column35: As long as i am the first to acquire the licenses of top selling and popular video games and guarantee a distribution exclusivity, I would be ahead of any competition at least for the first 36 months. Soon enough, the company will start by developing video games in house both for consoles and the internet and take the advantage over any competitor that tries to catch on.
column36: I would estimate that the company would break even after 24 months. The budget for the first year would be mainly spent on acquiring the video game licenses, setting up the studio, developing the website and finalizing the product. The second year"s budget would be spent mainly on marketing, distribution creating a sales force and continuing to acquire licenses.
column37: I would estimate that the first sale would be made 8-10 months after i start.
column38: The lack of experience is the major risk that is running against me. I plan to be surrounded by experienced advisers and consult some risk management firms. The online purchasing behavior is still not very popular in the Middle East and if the rate does not grow exponentially in the near future it would affect my marketing strategy, therefore, online advertising should not be the soul, instead should be included in the global marketing strategy of the company.

In summary, we will be establishing a branch of Academy of Health education in Lebanon to educate, treat, rehabilitate addictions, includes but not limited to alcohol / drugs / compulsive disorders such as food and gambling addictions. Further, to treat and educate community on aspects of stress management, meditation, anxiety and depression. The aim is to change attitudes towards a more positive approach to life, a better perception, to move, touch and inspire and create a transformation for the better throughout the middle east.
column26: The general community as a whole, particularly, those suffering from afflictions relating but not limited to alcohol, drug, food, gambling or other addictions. Diabetes awareness, nutritional education and treatment, depression and anxiety, stress management, meditation. This includes people as young as 16 to the older or much older community. Furthermore, there is a push in the Orient and the middle east towards junk food, fast food, recreational drug use, hard party drugs. The purpose of this mission is to target the communities most vulnerable, such as those from vulnerable educational, social or economical backgrounds and also those with genetic predisposition to such afflictions.

Mission and Philosophy well detailed along with CV of founder Dr. Robert Kaldawi (Ph. D).
In summary, we will be establishing a branch of Academy of Health education in Lebanon to educate, treat, rehabilitate addictions, includes but not limited to alcohol / drugs / compulsive disorders such as food and gambling addictions. Further, to treat and educate community on aspects of stress management, meditation, anxiety and depression. The aim is to change attitudes towards a more positive approach to life, a better perception, to move, touch and inspire and create a transformation for the better throughout the middle east.
column26: The general community as a whole, particularly, those suffering from afflictions relating but not limited to alcohol, drug, food, gambling or other addictions. Diabetes awareness, nutritional education and treatment, depression and anxiety, stress management, meditation. This includes people as young as 16 to the older or much older community. Furthermore, there is a push in the Orient and the middle east towards junk food, fast food, recreational drug use, hard party drugs. The purpose of this mission is to target the communities most vulnerable, such as those from vulnerable educational, social or economical backgrounds and also those with genetic predisposition to such afflictions.
column27: Entire of Lebanon at the start and then, proceed to cover the Middle East and the Arab World as required and necessary.
column28: Whilst there is no provision for commercial gains at this stage, the purpose is to help people and later to spread the word of health and positiveness. This in turn will be followed by power of word of mouth and benefit of health and liufestyle improvement across the entire community. Those in need will be treated free of charge, those who can afford it, will pay a fee per consultation. The estimate income is around half a million USD per year.

column25: Our company will provide a website which connects people who want to learn a topic(such a language, or resume writing), with educators in the global community who have knowledge on the topic. This community based learning approach allows anyone to play the role of both educator and learner. We will provide the technology to connect learners and educators and facilitate remote learning.
column26: Our target clients will be primarily high school and university aged people(16-30)  who are computer literate, own a PC, and have access to an internet connection.We expect to appeal mainly to people who are typically familiar with social networking sites such as Facebook and Twitter.
column27: Our target market will be major urban areas with high schools and universities. We will target mainly gulf countries where the level of internet usage is the highest, especially amongst high-school and university aged students, and where the average disposable income amongst this age group is the highest.
column28: We estimate the advertisement market on websites to be around $5,000,000 in 2009 from direct advertisements or through 3rd parties. As for the market of typical elearning websites it"s less than that, around $100,000.
column29: Our service is unique and isn"t offered anywhere in the world because we adopt a social networking approach to learning and allow users to connect with any educators in the global community to learn about any topic of their interest.  That being said,  we will still compete indirectly with online learning schools such as onlinelearning.net which typically offer certificate programs for individuals wishing to learn a particular trade for future work. Additionally we we will be competing with local schools and universities which offer tutoring, extracurricular programs, and workshops.
column30: We offer our clients the ability to choose educators based on a variety of factors such as geographical proximity, client ratings and reviews, language of instruction, time of course offerings, and methods of instruction (audio, video, in person). Unlike our competitors, this effectively allows our clients to tailor a course to their personal needs. Additionally since we are a social networking site, we will scale better. This means as the user base grows, so do the number of educators, and the variety and number of courses offered. Additionally, a growing user base also allows for healthy competition between educators competing for students, and this effectively should drive our prices lower than our competitors over the long run.
column35:
13- How long (in months) do you believe you can maintain your advantage over the competition until they match your product / service? (6 lines max | 6 points )

Until our service becomes popular enough to draw competitors, we believe we remain unrivaled in the area of social networking and online learning. We believe that after we hit our break even point, and become profitable, it will be at least 6 months before any competitor emerges. And this estimate is based on the time it takes to develop, deploy, and popularize a website similar to ours.

    The Milkshakes can be served either with or without whip-cream, and will be served with a hard piece of the chosen chocolate bar on the top layer of the drink.
   The serving cups will be of three sizes; small, medium and large, with special names: Pebble (small), Stone (medium), and Rock (large).
    The idea behind the business is fun drinks that can satisfy people by quenching their cravings for their favorite chocolate bars, only this time, shaken and crunched into refreshing, creative drinks!
    To keep costs low, we will initially base our sales approach on take away and drive through, with the possibility of expanding it to a seating area depending on the degree of success.

column30:
The advantages that make our product suitable and competitive in its target market are:
- It provides statistical information, useful for medical research and for the development of the health industry
- It is localized (i.e. available in Arabic)
- It is affordable
- Data management becomes easier in digital format
- The application has multiple interfaces with different privileges (i.e. head of unit, doctor, secretary...)
- It has a calendar feature with the option of sending automated sms messages to both patients and doctors
- It saves office space by ridding doctors from paper documents
- It is environmentally friendly :)

In Phase 2:
- It collects "anonymized" patients data from participating physicians, and gathers them in a centralized database in order to generate more representative statistics
- The centralized database allows us to link the doctors application with the laboratories in order to improve the medical care QOS

column25: It provides a solution called "Easy Patients Manager" that helps physicians identify their patients (Biometric ID), manage their files, keep track of their medical history, print their prescriptions, etc. The application also allows the user to process the collected data into useful statistical information to be used in potential future research studies. column29:
- We do not have direct competitors in Lebanon, as companies which develop similar applications target bigger institutions (i.e. Hospitals)

column30:
The advantages that make our product suitable and competitive in its target market are:
- It provides statistical information, useful for medical research and for the development of the health industry
- It is localized (i.e. available in Arabic)
- It is affordable
- Data management becomes easier in digital format
- The application has multiple interfaces with different privileges (i.e. head of unit, doctor, secretary...)
- It has a calendar feature with the option of sending automated sms messages to both patients and doctors
- It saves office space by ridding doctors from paper documents
- It is environmentally friendly :)

In Phase 2:
- It collects "anonymized" patients data from participating physicians, and gathers them in a centralized database in order to generate more representative statistics
- The centralized database allows us to link the doctors application with the laboratories in order to improve the medical care QOS

column36:
Assuming that yearly sales are 100 programs (1% of the market), then the dollar value of these sales after x months of the 1st sale is 100 * (x / 12) * $800.
Total costs until then are: 9,500 (fixed) + 1,200*3*(9+x) (salaries for 3 engineers) + 600*x (salary for support technician) + 600*(9+x) (rent) + 150*(9+x) (office supplies) + 10,000 (marketing) =
Total profits until then are: 1,000*(x)*100/12 (sales)
x = 17 months to break even after the first sale.

column29:
There are no clear direct competitors for our services. Based on a recent market scan the following names are the well known players in the market. Each competitor provides a set of the services we provide but not the full package that we provide.
Ebtikar: Specialized in Low level design
BT Applied Technologies: End to end Solutions, however lack of proper integration with non traditional systems
Al-Saggaf Sons: Provides design service but mainly focus on moving their own products
TCS: Good consulting services but lacks understanding of local market needs

Our company will focus on micro payments in the arab countries(mobile and online payments). We will build solutions that will enable our end customers to pay their monthly bills online or through their mobiles. 

 The generation of revenue will focus on two channels: The first channel is through selling the developed and customized payment solution to companies to enable their end users to pay their bills.  
The second channel is by taking a commisision for every payment done through our payment infrastrucutre.
column26: End users who wish to pay their bills through a fast, easy and convenient way. Example: Mobile & telephone bills, electricity bill, tickets, rent bill, water bill, etc.. All kinds of payments.
column27: We will first target Lebanon and the GCC countries first. We will then expand to cover all other arabian countries. Then, we will expand to target underdeveloped countries where the banking sector is not that reliable - basically african countries.

column25: The company"s aim is to provide retail outlets and consumers with a profiling environment that builds a personal purchase and shopping experience for the consumer, and a tracking and interaction database for businesses. The company will design, integrate and maintain the hardware and software necessary for this link between the business and the consumer.
column26:
Target clients focus includes frequent shoppers searching for new products from associated businesses, and individuals with need for a frequent certain product setting, to be quickly realized, maybe automatically, by the associated business. An example for the fist case would be shopping for garments, while for the second case would be buying the usual coffee configuration.
There are no certain age groups or segment of clients initially targeted. The aim is to develop the technology behind the end product and to search for main associates that would drive the application of this technology in different retail segments.
column27: The first associates should be corporate retailers that span on several branches in several cities. This is followed by local retailers in large cities that join with benefits and as the technology proves itself. Focus will be on malls in big cities, with new malls founded rapidly containing several chain businesses.
column28: It is hard to estimate the success of a breakthrough technology. An estimate would be anywhere between 100k USD to 1 million USD, depending on successful business associations.
column29:
The technology will compete with online retail, which is practically another approach, usually feared as insecure and not localized within the region.
There are several customer loyalty cards that are occasionally offered for free at stores and subscription cards that allow for discounts at several stores per card. These methods have proven not to be successful and are not interactive, not allowing the experience for the buyer and the customer link with the reseller.
column30: The planned merit found by the end-consumer is the ability to link previous shopping experiences with current ones, and through development of the merchant"s database, be provided with personalized products that can make the shopping experience easier and faster. The merit for the associated businesses is to recieve a ready infrastructure to build databases based on client behaviour, allowing for better product delivery through decreasing human error and facilitating purchase survey. Our final product will retail at a low cost for the consumer, while businesses join the network through lending of hardware and customizable IT infrastructures. This is attainable through utalizing outsourced hardware specifically configured, with low costs, for this concept.

column25: The idea here is to provide the community with an internet service that will allow people to know more about medications, their use, side effects, and gain some advise from practitioners. This project will serve as a database for pharmaceutical products in the Egyptian market, and will evolve into a database for customers as well as physicians. It will also serve as a launch pad for pharmaceutical advertising through the internet. In the future, it will also evolve into an online ordering pharmacy, which would benefit patients across the country.

column24: The headquarter will be in the historical city of Beirut which will be known from now on as the new city of Fashion and creativity. We are planning to open offices and retails in all the GCC countries.
column25: The ICONIC concept consists of nurturing the creativity of our young Arab designers and opens for them the doors to realize their dreams and be able to show to the world that we have talented Arab designers and we will create the new trends of tomorrow in a very fashionable way thus conveying and transferring to all the world our culture and our potential in a very beautiful and peaceful way thus we are going to enable those designers in a very intelligent and efficient way to face to the competition of the huge fast fashion mass products that doesnâ€™t take into consideration the preferences nor the cultural fingerprint of the people in each countries. Today all the Arab designers will have the opportunity to create a piece of art a fashion item ( such as cloth or an accessories in one or more categories: handbags, accessories, wardrobe, Ready-to-wear, Jewels),then all those designs will be posted on the ICONIC website which will be marketed through creating a viral marketing campaign thus saving money that will be invested more efficiently in other area, where the customers will enter the website and vote to the best designers and rank the products. The top products that receive the highest score will be manufactured and sold at the ICONIC  website and unique stores where the customers will find the most exclusive and fashionable products that meets best theirs tastes in a great environment where they will have the chance to meet the designers of their cloths in the shop where there will be an open space where some designers will always be present and working (designing, drawing, cuttingâ€¦)thus the customers will see the world of the designers. In addition to we should mention that we are using the internet voting in order to be able to collect information of our customers thus targeting them better, and we should not forget the amount of Publicity we will receive as well the word of mouth marketing that will be created through this competition where each designer will tell his friend about the conceptâ€¦
column26: As a beginning our stores will target women that are between the age of 18 and 35 years that have an acceptable purchasing power and are willing to pay on average 35% higher than they would pay for at the usual fast fashion shops such as Vero Moda or H&M. Our target market at this age will be probably working and having additional income and usually is ready to spent larger amount of money for shopping, moreover during this age women are open to change and are ready to try something new , they need to looks unique and up-to-date not only wearing like everyone the low quality products that today are almost the same in all the stores , those products that doesn"t take in consideration a lot the taste diffrence between Occident. and the Arab countries.We choose to position ourselves in the mind of the customer as delivering better Quality as well Unique and Fashionable clothes that will fit the best its taste at every moment and occasions.

My ICONIC concept was born when we were able to see a Real need and an underserved market which is very large thus we would be operating at a very efficient way in the short and long term.

After sensing this need we used more scientific approach to be able to make sure that what we saw is real and there is a real opportunity, thatâ€™s why we did for long time research studies and used proper marketing research tools such as survey (more than 311 people filled our survey, we did interviews with 87 people to be able to know and understand their purchasing behavior and what they believe is missed in this industry and asked them what we could to fulfill their needs and improve the way they shop, and used some observational research to validate our previous results).

column25:
WRB GROUP will buy a 4-ha land in Benslimane, 60 km from Casablanca.
We plan to build 10 houses on stilts, these houses can accommodate from 2 to 6 people with every comfort known to every house (bedrooms, kitchenette, bathrooms, toilets, laundry, balcony, central heating...).
The project will be fully equipped with environmental facilities (Treatment Plant Wastewater, solar panels, gas water heater and only the steam room will be heated with wood).
For restoration, we expect that building a hostel for cooking day dishes is the most user friendly way of participatory spirit, collecting and cooking own farm fruits and vegetables.
In addition to the guest house, a large lounge & dining room, a large patio where people can relax, meet, exchange or enjoy a mint tea.
column26:
Every kind of people, but asthmatic people should be our first target because the climate in Benslimane is very beneficial for them.
All people who have respiratory failure, disease or illness we find a haven of peace and health in our land.
The second target is people who suffer from obesity, homeland will teach them how to manage them selves, relearn how to live, relearn how to eat and the most important thing is learn how to do physical exercises (Dina Alami is also certified as an NLP coach)
We will establish activities such as rides horse, racetrack on foot, mountain bike trail, archery, not forgetting a little gardening and impromptu picnics all around the land.
Our cottage will have a dormitory for backpackers; our third targeted clients; many clubs are very active in the last years and they visit Benslimane as a nice area for picnic and rest.
column27:
Europe: because Europeans likes Morocco, they look for ecotourism and the supply does not match the demand.
United States & Canada: the North American are unfamiliar with Morocco, most of them think that Morocco is a Asian country
Middle East: because they know normal and luxury tourism but never gone beyond it, I am proposing a real new tourism based on nature and environment.
column28:
Morocco welcomes every year 7.5 million of tourists. With a total turnover of more than 8 million dollars.
Morocco attracts almost 15 million overnight stays in classified establishments, so our market is located around 2 or 3% of total occupancy in Morocco. In dollar terms, that means 160.000 dollars.
column29:
High Atlas: 6 houses and breakfast (2 Ait Bougmez Valley,1 Anergui Valley, 1 Toubkal National Park, 1 Geographic MGoun Park, & the last near a mountain river in front of Dades Valley)
Middle Atlas: 2 bed and breakfast in Aguelmane Sidi Ali Lake & Ifrane
The Rif mountain range: only one in Talassemtane National Park
All of these houses and properties are basic with traditional materials, simple but comfortable.
column30:
Healthy air, fresh food, local products, not even one motor in the farm. Ecotourism has a certain and prosper future.
All cooking will be in wood oven, bread will be prepared everyday with natural products from the farm.
What I am planning to have, is a real eco-tourist land with no car, no motor, no petrol.
column35:
Not all the investors are attracted by the ecotourism, it"s been too long that this type of tourism exists, but in Morocco there are few people who believed it"s a good idea.
In Benslimane, no one invested in this type of tourism and I will be pleased to offer this type of service for the hundreds of people who are waiting for this initiative
column36: Break-even will be reached after 6 years of operation if 10 houses are launched in the beginning of the business. column38:
The major risks that can work against my projects are the economic fluctuations, if so; people can not plan holidays in my farm.
There is also the Benslimane Airport project; it has to be achieved and direct flights should be programmed from at least two cities in each continent.
In the other hand, two positive points are helping my business plan; the roads are being completed, we are moving from a situation of a two-way road to a twice double road; also national and secondary roads are in the Plan Planning.
All the ingredients are held to improve the city of Benslimane and the major risks are to stop these investments.

column25: The main concept for this proposal is to conduct an eco-tourism project in Lebanon, which consists of opening a green resort on the coastline. The business aims to promote eco-tourism in Lebanon, since it is at its early stages in the region. PILOT ECO-HOLIDAYS can be a pioneer in entering this segment in Lebanon, developing it, and expanding it into other countries in the region, knowing that it is a very profitable business over the long term.
column26: The main targeted segment for this hotel is the tourists, which are named â€œthe alternative touristsâ€. They are the tourists, who can be characterized by: trying to avoid the beaten track; going places nobody has set foot in before, bringing a senses of adventure, seeking to forget civilization for a while, establishing contacts with local people, tend to remain in the country for more days than more traditional tourists.In addition, there is another main target for this project which is the Lebanese diaspora around the world. It is estimated that the Lebanese diaspora is over 12 million persons. If the hotel can attract 2% of this diaspora, I think it will be enough to expand this project into other regions in Lebanon, and into other countries in the region.
column27: There is no specific Geographic target market since our hotel aims at attracting guests from all over the world. therefore, our planning, and execution will be done while taking into consideration that we will receive guests from all over the world seeking to have the experience of a natural retreat, and to get the knowledge of green hospitality and its benefits.
column28: taking into consideration that european individuals spend an average of 5000$ on their holidays, The increase of domestic tourism in lebanon, and the new plans of the ministry of tourism to attract tourists from all over the world, we would estimate the size of the market as 2 Billion Dollars/year market.
column29:
Our direct competitors in the market are all the environmental-friendly establishments which has the objective of promoting environmental activities, and awareness. These competitors have our same target marke. examples of these competitors are:
PEAKS Hotel/Faytroun, Le Refuge/Afqa. 
On the other hand, we have indirect competitors which are all types of resorts and hotels on the coastline which may attract any type of tourists. examples of this type of competitors are: Las Salinas/Anfeh, San Stephano Resort/Batroun, Edde Resort/Jbeil.
However, PILOT HOTEL have a lot of competitive advantages in order to overcome these obstacles.
column30:
The hotel will be a 150-room hotel with the opportunity to have outdoor camps in the wild. The construction of the hotel will be based on natural products, such as wood, fabrics, and there is no use whatsoever of cement, and concrete.
The Basic Hotel activities consist of the following: Climbing, Hiking, Cycling, Horseback riding, Archery, Rope course, Orienteering, Bird-watching.Since we are working on an eco-tourism project, than all the eco-tourism features, and aspects have to be taken into consideration. These aspects include:
1.Radically increase the productivity of resource
2.Shift to biologically inspired production 
3. Invest in natural and human capital. 
4. Select responsible suppliers.  
5. Product service system
column35: The project consists of three main phases. The first phase is that during the first 30 month, the first property shall be opened in Batroun. The second phase consists of that within 2.5 years of operation other 4 properties shall be opened in other regions of Lebanon, and some of them are in sea zones cities. Therefore, we believe that we can maintain our advantage for a period of 5 years over the competition.
column36: In our opinion, the first year will be a testing year in the market since the product we are offering is new, and the market is still young. However, taking into consideration the awareness over Environmental Friendly activities, and the potential annual 15% growth of the market, we would estimate that it would require 18 months before the company breaks even.
column37: The suggested time to finish the first phase of the project is 30 months. It consists of 18 months of construction, 6 months staffing, and 6 months for pilot opening.
column39: Lebanon is the master of hospitality among the Arab world. Its hospitality schools, and universities are considered as the basic source for all the hospitality institutions around the region. Based on all these characteristics of Lebanon, and its people, I think it is important to conduct an eco-tourism project of this importance here, and consider Lebanon as the starting point to expand into other countries of the regions.
column40: With the rapid awareness of enivronmental friendly activities in lebanon, we would estimate a 15% annual growth of the market.
column42: Since PILOT HOTEL will be the pioneer in this line of business, we are planning to capture 40% of the market share in the first 5 years.
column43: It is estimated the average room rate is 130$, and an assumed 3% inflation rate has been applied going forward to the year 2015.We shall also have 8,447,000$ of gross operating income

How many times have we sought objective assistance in terms of determining what convenes us most without receiving any accurate input? column27: Initiated a low budget Market Study, that was human resourced and strategically driven and that didn"t require professionals in order to cut terms on budget. The study consisted of identifying dissected areas that are targeted for our product positioning, and discerning the nature of the market in terms of the Brands exposed in that area, the pricing affiliated to them, the social nature of the targeted audience. It also included the spending habits of the customers in that area, projecting potential income generated in that market, detecting marketing activities that future rivals are engaged in, and the market share of each of the competitors with the accorded SWOT analysis.

For that to happen in a continuous competitive advantage:
â€¢	Conduct weekly researches Online and in the local market (stores, magazines, fashion shows etcâ€¦) after spotting the nucleus source of fashion generators. These researches should be assessed on specific criteria and reported thoroughly to the purchasing manager. It is crucial to keep track of all updates of Fashion. (Seasonâ€™s trends, colors, pricing portfolio, prospects feedback etcâ€¦)  This will represent the Marketing intelligence, one of the most vital and affective sections of the decision-making process. It should be handled by experienced professionals with an insight on the companyâ€™s overall mission.

â€¢	Spot exclusive sources of high quality wears for modest pricing. Finishing is the most important criteria with the source designation, that is, after granting the quality elegance and effectiveness.
Potential sources could be locally, Europe (Italy, Turkey, and France) and Far East.
To settle with exclusive suppliers and initiate a long term relationship with them, testing of the material and their work should be very accurate and basic based on sampling and mini orders; it should include testing areas such as: 
-Quality		-Finishing	-Time commitment	-Costing	         -Honesty	
Recognizing such factories by relying on the internet and some market studies.

column25:
eldaftar, is the first nhanc turnkey solution that includes all essential modules to run any SMB effectively ranging from step-by-step startup business guidelines to SMBs laws and regulations knowledge library, startup entrepreneur communities & Social Network integration, bookkeeping, payroll, stock control, business consultation and more.
With its built-in business advisor, eldaftar can help SMBs owners in understanding the consequences of their management decisions in addition to enabling them to manage their business more effectively and profitably. In addition to eldaftar available vertical solutions, eldaftar could be branded and integrated with other readymade business partners solutions (Vodafone Egypt â€œelmodeerâ€ business case).
column27: - Egypt ICT indicator Portal
column36: First production year should be highly dedicated to software development. Entry barrier is not high which poses a continuous threat that needs to be addressed continuously through tremendous efforts to keep the product on the top. lots of effort should be done to deliver innovative application add-ons, new features and focus on customer stickiness specially in the first six months of customer adoption.
column37: The value proposition is to deliver reliable cloud-based IT solutions for SMB at an affordable cost with no infrastructure requirements. The challenge for SMBs to advance from an IT perspective is to start acquiring the needed infrastructure such as servers, network and needed applications. Seeking international solutions doesnâ€™t help because of the language barrier as well as the local culture needs from different perspectives such as accounting standards (examples competing are quicken and Peachtree). eldaftar and potential new nhanc offerings will dramatically reduce the cost, headache and effort to run a reliable IT solution for this market.
column40: nhanc will focus on three primary markets during 2011-2012. These markets are Egypt, Saudi Arabia and United Arab Emirates. As the initial local market, the SMB market size in Egypt is not officially quantified due to varying data from different government sources.. The unofficial forecasts are in the range of 500,000 SMBs in major cities. The Egyptian ICT indicators portal indicates that business including SMBs who are using the internet reached 35% by July 2009. Sub segmentation of the SMBs in each market is another needed step to help in positioning eldaftar correctly. These sub-segments are expected to be small (0-25 employees), medium (26-50 employees) and large (51-99 employees). Each of these will require a significant level of variation on the online platform and a smooth transition from one step to the other in catering the exponential growth of any successful SMB.
column43:
nhanc is promoting eldaftar using a selective distribution channel model to achieve its goal of generating profitable and sustainable revenue stream. This model could be classified into two types according to the target segment:-

1)For SME, the business model for the platform
â€¢	Long term monthly subscription fees 
â€¢	Platform add-ons as major revenue stream

2)For Large enterprise, the business model for the platform
â€¢	Advertising to eldaftar SME customers as a revenue source
â€¢	Eldaftar extension agreements (Distribution and Order Management) ex. Unilever, P&G
â€¢	Analytics reporting revenue

column25: We are proud to introduce our service as an online grocery shopping and shipping system which can provide a brand new experience to the shoppers who don"t have much time to spend on grocery shopping after work. The idea of the service is simple. We are planning to incorporate with large-sized international supermarket such as Carrefour and build an online supermarket which allows the shoppers to select all kinds of grocery through the company"s website and to make their payment online. By simply spending few seconds to click instead of driving and being in a crowed market after a busy day, our customers can relax at home and wait their grocery to be shipped in next day !
column27:
Online shopping has been a competitive market trend in all industries for now and for long-term future based on fast-growing numbers of computer users and the change of life style. Therefore, this business is expected to be largely expanded
and revenue generating according to time.
column32: Since this idea is very original and unique, we have not yet found a direct competitor in the same industry;however, the indirect competitors are traditional supermarkets and other online shopping websites.

This information includes name, credit card number, (actual and email)address, and phone number.

It"s a turbine which is operated by solids.The first advantage of this turbine that it will give maximum extraction power.The second advantage is that we may use sands falling from high levels such as mountains or digging a big hole and put the turbine in the down.The biggest advantage of this idea that it can be used to make use from solid wastes such as any metal industrial wastes,old cars and any metallic solid wastes.We can compress these wastes into blocks and manufacture a huge solid turbine with suitable blades design to be operated by these blocks as they fall under gravity.So we can establish a wide solid turbine field with many solid turbines in the main area of solid turbine of the factories or the country and take extracted power from these wastes.
finally, this is the main idea and the other details will be developed with the business plan and the main challenge is that no one developed this kind of turbine before so it is the first invention.

column25:
The majority of Middle Eastern businesses suffer a lot in the competition vs their counterparts in Asia, Europe and the Americas in the fact that they have very weak online presence and a great deal of disconnected internal business processes. Even though each company has a company website that describes their products and services, and usually each company has their own ERP system, this is far from enough. They need to "Go Digital" across the entire business value chain starting with the consumer, all the way back to the manufacturing process. Going digital is a much talked about word nowadays, but in order to make the best out of digital, you need to bring together multidisciplinary knowledge, expertise and world class execution. Going digital is not just about procuring the latest and state of the art IT systems. 

"Digitize Arabia" will help you through every step of the process of going digital, be it in digitizing your companyâ€™s operations, creating an online strategy, going online, and managing your ongoing digital campaign from end to end. 

"Digitize Arabia" team follows a 360 degree approach and has a team with extensive business and marketing knowledge that enables us to see beyond the technical aspects of going online, and in identifying where the real opportunities are. We will create an entire Business Transformation plan across all functions in your organization in order to:
* Standardize, simplify and automate processes and systems
* Dramatically reduce time to market 
* Create a digital workforce and digital work environment
* Equip your organization to better deal with online customers, online suppliers and online  influencers

* Dramatically reduce time to market 
* Create a digital workforce and digital work environment
* Equip your organization to better deal with online customers, online suppliers and online  influencers

The majority of Middle Eastern businesses suffer a lot in the competition vs their counterparts in Asia, Europe and the Americas in the fact that they have very weak online presence and a great deal of disconnected internal business processes. Even though each company has a company website that describes their products and services, and usually each company has their own ERP system, this is far from enough. They need to "Go Digital" across the entire business value chain starting with the consumer, all the way back to the manufacturing process. Going digital is a much talked about word nowadays, but in order to make the best out of digital, you need to bring together multidisciplinary knowledge, expertise and world class execution. Going digital is not just about procuring the latest and state of the art IT systems. 

"Digitize Arabia" will help you through every step of the process of going digital, be it in digitizing your companyâ€™s operations, creating an online strategy, going online, and managing your ongoing digital campaign from end to end. 

"Digitize Arabia" team follows a 360 degree approach and has a team with extensive business and marketing knowledge that enables us to see beyond the technical aspects of going online, and in identifying where the real opportunities are. column25:
@sama is an online portal for airline ticket reservation. Due to the increase of the number of carriers in the region, especially low-cost airlines, there has been an increase demand for a tool that will allow the customers to compare fairs and book the cheapest. 

@Sama is an innovative portal that will integrate with all the airlines in the region.
column27:
The global competitors such as expedia.com, kayak.com, and cheaptickets.com are only integrated with the more established carriers. However, the price sensitive users are more interested in comparing fares from the low-cost carriers. Also, most of the customers who use the standard carriers have more brand loyalty, and are not sensitive to price. 

We have identified this gap, and have surveyed 500 customers from all over the middle east, and the response was very promising. They all said that they will buy from @sama as long as we don"t add a service charge to the price.  

Here is a very interesting statistic. The volume of eCommerce transactions in the Arab World during 2009 was slightly above 1 Billion US Dollars. Quit a big number, however more than 50% of this amount is actually airline tickets. This proves that most customers like to buy their tickets online, its a great opportunity !
column40:
Our geographic target Market is the Arab World, with a special focus on the GCC. 

Our target customer persona is as follows: 
- Price sensitive
- Works in a country other than his/her own 
- Between the age of 25 and 50 years of age. 
- Might be single or married.
column43:
Our revenue model will be in the form of a flat fee commission from the airlines. Airlines are already giving travel agencies commissions, and they wouldn"t mind giving @sama the same commission. 

This revenue model is well established in the global markets and works really well. The customers end up getting great prices, and don"t have to pay more. 

Consider the following: Southwest Airlines a well established US airline has a market capitalization of $3 Billion US dollars. Cheaptickets.com a company that uses the same revenue model that @Sama will use has a market cap of $15 Billion US Dollars in the Nasdaq exchange.
column51:
The innovation that @Sama brings is related to how it will integrate with the new low-cost airlines that have been appearing lately in region specially in the GCC. 

Our tools will support XML integration with cron-job updates, in addition to manual integrations with Legacy systems.

column25: Each month, hundreds of thousands of Jordanian households receive an electricity bill under the door, which they must pay at a government office, a post office, or a bank.  In a similar light, any parking or traffic ticket a citizen receives must be paid in person at a specific government office.  In our view, this is inefficient for the citizens and costly for both the citizens and government alike.  We propose to contract with government entities such as the utility company and the traffic patrol office to set up an online service for citizens to pay their utility bills and parking tickets.  This would be a major convenience for the citizens, and it would be very cost effective for the government as the online platform would cut the costs typical in a brick and mortar operation (rent, utilities, labor, etc).
column27: We have spoken to many Jordanians who agree that it is much simpler and more effective to log on to the internet and pay a bill than it is to drive to a local office and wait in line, only to do the same.  We have studied the market in the United States where similar services exist.  Most importantly, we are in discussions with executives at the incumbent Jordan utility regarding the possibility of offering this service.
column29: Market growth is best estimated by nominal GDP growth, which is roughly 3.2%.  This number is further compounded by the dramatic increase in internet penetration (it more than doubled from 2007 to 2009 and is expected to reach 50% by the end of 2011).

Through discussion with various software developers, as well as our knowledge of programming, server maintenance, and hosting from previous work on internet businesses, we estimate the costs as follows:

Programming costs: $37,500; we reach this number by multiplying 500 hours of programming, testing, security testing, etc. by the $75 rate we would pay for top of the market programmers

Server fees: $1,000 a month for a dedicated server whereby 99.99% uptime is guaranteed.

Marketing expense: $20,000; because incentives are aligned with the government in that costs are reduced when citizens pay their bills online, the utility and traffic authority will promote the service.  This alleviates our marketing expense, but test campaigns could be beneficial.
column32: The greatest potential competitor would be the government itself if it chose to operate the online service on its own as opposed to outsource it. It would not be in the interest of the government to do so given the cost savings and efficiency of outsourcing information technology (IT) processes.
column36: The competitive advantage will be maintained only by cooperation with the government to be the incumbent supplier of this online service.  Otherwise, barriers to entry are low and other companies can offer their own software at a lower commission for citizens to pay their bills.  Only by partnering with local governments and being regarded as the dominant, incumbent supplier will success build upon success and prevent entry of competition.
column37: The competitor, or status quo of going somewhere to make a payment, is inefficient, inconvenient, and outdated.  Secure online payments will transform several bothersome errands into a few clicks.
column38: The electrical company, government, and other organizations receiving payments may eliminate the middle man (us) and offer secure online payment services directly to the customer.  By creating a single portal for all payments, however, we reduce this risk.
column40:
The target country is initially Jordan, a country in which we were born and have knowledge of local customs as well as relationships with people in various industries.  The business has ability to expand, but unbridled growth will be detrimental.  Instead, we wish to focus in Jordan first, and become the dominant (hopefully only) service supplier to the government, thus creating barriers to entry for competitors.

Our target customers are the population of Jordan that receives an electricity bill or parking ticket and has easy access to the internet. Currently, internet penetration is over 36% and rapidly rising.
column42:
For the electrical bill component:
Population of Jordan: 6 million people
Households in Jordan: ~1 million
Internet users: 1,741,000
Internet penetration: 36%
People paying bills each month: 360,000
Average bill: $60 dollars
Total yearly bill payment: 360,000 * $60 * 12 months = $259,200,000
Commission (2%): 2% of $259,200,000 = $5,184,000
column43: We will earn a commission of 2% or so from each transaction.  We are in the process of calculating the total costs for the government to offer a standard bricks and mortar operation with desk attendants to serve the population.  Because this business is only viable if the government a) chooses to allow an online platform and b) chooses to have it outsourced, the price (i.e., our commission) must be lower than its current cost to serve the community.
column51:
It is a mainstay of Jordanian life to head to a government office, a post office, or bank each month to pay the electricity bill.  It is also a fact of life that any parking or traffic violation must be resolved in person.  Our service would simplify this process as citizens would be afforded the opportunity to pay their bills or tickets online.

The convenience to the citizenry is obvious, and so is the cost effectiveness to the government.  An online portal could eliminate many jobs where government employees serve the long lines of people waiting to pay a bill.  Instead, these employees can be moved to other jobs in other areas of the economy where they can potentially have a higher productivity.  Of course the cost to the government would be a fraction of the value of each transaction.  But the savings would exceed the cost: one study in the United States valued the cost of processing an online transaction at a mere $1.60 as opposed to the $6.60 it cost for a counter transaction.  Instead of paying rent, electricity, labor, etc., the government would instead pay a fraction of each transaction.  Furthermore, in addition to reducing costs, this service has the potential to increase government revenues, as many people simply do not pay parking tickets due to the time and hassle associated with doing so.
column52: When the website is fully operational, citizens will utilize the service as soon as they learn about it.  Few people would prefer to take a drive to pay a bill rather than go online and pay it in a few easy clicks.

column25: Each month, hundreds of thousands of Jordanian households receive an electricity bill under the door, which they must pay at a government office, a post office, or a bank.  In a similar light, any parking or traffic ticket a citizen receives must be paid in person at a specific government office.  In our view, this is inefficient for the citizens and costly for both the citizens and government alike.  We propose to contract with government entities such as the utility company and the traffic patrol office to set up an online service for citizens to pay their utility bills and parking tickets.  This would be a major convenience for the citizens, and it would be very cost effective for the government as the online platform would cut the costs typical in a brick and mortar operation (rent, utilities, labor, etc).
column27: We have spoken to many Jordanians who agree that it is much simpler and more effective to log on to the internet and pay a bill than it is to drive to a local office and wait in line, only to do the same.  We have studied the market in the United States where similar services exist.  Most importantly, we are in discussions with executives at the incumbent Jordan utility regarding the possibility of offering this service.

column25:
the european center for islamic finance ( ECIF) has the purpose to study islamic finance in europe.

1) create a monthly newspaper about a specific subjet in  islamic finance

As you may know, islamic finance is not well known in Europe, and we would like to spread it by making publications in french and in english

2) create a database including all european companies where it"s not haram to make investments 

3)study the possibility to see how the islamic banks could be etablished in europe

a) which countries has the best economic environemment for islamic banks ?

b) what economic and legal obstructions stand in the way of islamic banks to make their etablishment on the european ground ?

c) studying the project to etablish a belgian islamic bank to receive deposits of muslim people without interest

d)make connections with worlwide universities teaching islamic finance to allow future students to study over there.

e) study the possibility for new islamic products
column27:
1) We have been studying the legal environment in Belgium
2) we made research on the different universites teaching islamic finance
3) we have made some research on economic environment in belgium 
4) we have asked some people from all levels to see if they would be interested by putting their money in islamic banks
5) we have asked to some specialist in charia, in economics, in finance, in law, if they would collaborate with us once the ecif will be etablished.

6)we made some research to see if this project has been created by someone else
column51:
the idea of  creating the ECIF is very innovative because in europe , we don"t have acces to islamic finance.

Muslim people keep thinking that the only way to make projects and create companies in belgium or europe , is to ask money from occidental banks.

they also think that nowadays, wa can not survivre in this occidental society without being involved in loans with interest.

They have a poor knowledge on islamic finance. Some people would like to know more about islamic finance but all books are written in english or in arabic. Some people too would like islamic banks to handle and to take care of their money.

But infortunately, we have no banks involved in islamic finance.

Our contribution is to make easier the access to islamic finance and why not to create a small islamic bank.

another contribution will be to create a database for all people willing to make investments on financial markets.

further,a significative contribution is to prepare, giving advices to people who want to study islamic finance abroad and why not giving foundation courses.

thiss project could be launched thanks to the winning price.

column25: To establish a company for Digital Audio Production in the field of Audio Books, focusing on Arabic content, either from translated titles or original Arabic titles. The scope of products will start with Self Improvement & Social/Business Improvement titles, to extend later to cover all available content suitable for Audio Books production. The production will cover the Audio content material preparation, recording, processing, packaging & distribution.
column27:
1- Online Survey that reached 1600 hits online (http://freeonlinesurveys.com/rendersurvey.asp?sid=g67oplqu2c91hdm844896) to collect the needed proof of our assumption of the opportunity.
2- Contacted 4 customers of the targeted customers segment. All of them showed interest, two of them are ready t sign the NDA, one is waiting for the prototype and a financial offer.
column29: We expect a percentage of 20% growth given that our books library will increase by 100 new books per year.
column30: We will buy books royalties, with down payment of US$1200 per book,  with 20 titles (books) to produce during the first 8 months. One book production will cost around US$1500.
column40:
We will target the Arab World region in specific, and all Arabic speakers in general.
Our early adopters will be the Corporates in the Arab world that have more than 50 employees, and spend more than US$3000 per year on training & HR development.
Our early majority will be the Mobiles/Smart Phones users who can access VAS content and Internet.
column42:
Arabic Speakers who do not speak English are around 100,000,000 in count. More than 70,000,000 of them own or at least have access to a device that can play a digital audio media. We expect 1% of that number to adopt our products. With an annual growth of 1%.

Assuming our targeted production volume of a 100 books per year in the first three years, and assuming the average price of the copy is US$10.
Number of copies sales per year = 100 X 1% X 1,400,000 = 1,400,000 copies.
Size of our Market = 10 X 1,400,000 = US$ 14,000,000.
column43:
1- Contract Sales to corporates for Audio Books Bundles for employees improvement.
2- Online Download through www.masmoo3.com website, and though the iTunes stores.
3- Publishers will buy the Audio Books version of the printed books they publish, which Masmoo3 will produce. 
4- Mobiles/Smart-Phones WAB/Web & VAS channels subscription for split audio books download.
column51:
Audio books have become a major source of knowledge and its market has been growing over the past few years in Europe and USA, and audio books are expected to outsell paperback books or e-books one day because of their convenience in the modern busy life style people currently live, as they can be played anytime anywhere while people are walking, shopping or waiting in queues. 
Currently, Arabic audio books are not very common. You can rarely find a time management book, self improvement title, or best seller international novel available as an Arabic audio book, although they are widely available as Arabic printed paperback books.

Our early adopters will be the Corporates in the Arab world that have more than 50 employees, and spend more than US$3000 per year on training & HR development.
Our early majority will be the Mobiles/Smart Phones users who can access VAS content and Internet.
column42:
Arabic Speakers who do not speak English are around 100,000,000 in count. More than 70,000,000 of them own or at least have access to a device that can play a digital audio media. We expect 1% of that number to adopt our products. With an annual growth of 1%.

Assuming our targeted production volume of a 100 books per year in the first three years, and assuming the average price of the copy is US$10.
Number of copies sales per year = 100 X 1% X 1,400,000 = 1,400,000 copies.
Size of our Market = 10 X 1,400,000 = US$ 14,000,000.
column43:
1- Contract Sales to corporates for Audio Books Bundles for employees improvement.
2- Online Download through www.masmoo3.com website, and though the iTunes stores.
3- Publishers will buy the Audio Books version of the printed books they publish, which Masmoo3 will produce. 
4- Mobiles/Smart-Phones WAB/Web & VAS channels subscription for split audio books download.
column51:
Audio books have become a major source of knowledge and its market has been growing over the past few years in Europe and USA, and audio books are expected to outsell paperback books or e-books one day because of their convenience in the modern busy life style people currently live, as they can be played anytime anywhere while people are walking, shopping or waiting in queues. 
Currently, Arabic audio books are not very common. You can rarely find a time management book, self improvement title, or best seller international novel available as an Arabic audio book, although they are widely available as Arabic printed paperback books.

column25:
The purpose of Eskuila is to provide a market place for on-line learning and a virtual platform for knowledge exchange.
Eskuila offers its users a web-interface that enables them to post their programs; be it a
course, a seminar or a training program, to present in its virtual classes. Participants will be able to search from a wide database of courses, trainings, educators, schools and coaches.
Eskuila leverages cloud-computing technologies to offer a reliable platform that can generate an unlimited number of virtual rooms and manage an unlimited number of participants.
Eskuila allows its users to choose from a variety of topics and disciplines from the comfort of their location, be it home, office or while on the move. Eskuila will reduce barriers to accessing education, such as cost and distance.

column25: Women"s wear which is modest, cool, comfortable, easy to wear, easy to wash and, most importantly, fashionable.
column27:
A. Canvassing of women from 15-45 to determine:
1. the difficulty they have in donning Islamic headcovering each morning which does not slip.
2. the level of comfort in the standard and designer abayas (silk and polyester)
3. the availability of competitive products on the market
column29:
The size of the market is unpredictable. It would change in accordance with the population growth in the geographical marketing regions, the growth of the Islamic populations in those regions, and tourism in those regions.
It is only the share of the market which is informed about the product which could be predictable.
column40:
To begin, the market would be Dubai, and then Abu Dhabi, and later the other UAE Emirates.  After some success in those markets, the GCC region would be included. Thirdly, the other Arab countries, and finally, the Michigan, United States, Munich Germany and other areas of the western countries which have high Muslim populations who speak English, Arabic, or German.
Target customers are: firstly, young (and young at heart) Muslimas from puberty to 40 who live in the hot climates of the Muslim-dominated world and who are required to wear (or who desire to wear) modest clothing.  Secondly, we would target western, Filipino and Russian women who want to be fashionable and yet modest, because they are married to Muslims and required by their husbands to wear modest clothing.
The third target market is tourists who want to wear some "traditional clothing", and still be comfortable and attractive.
column43:
The primary source of level during the first 1-2 years of business will be franchise fees to female marketers who host home fashion shows and serve as marketing mouthpieces for the fashion.
In the backup plan, the primary source of revenue would be from sales of basic items like patented Islamic head coverings, cool/washable abayas, and specially designed dickies
column51:
1. One of the flagship products is a new way of wearing Islamic headcovering which is much easier to wear without having to adjust it constantly.
2. A basic feature of several items  of the starting line of clothing features a woven moisture wicking fabric which drapes almost like silk. The fabric is not available on the market today.
3. Several items of the starting line of abayas feature detachable collars and cuffs - a feature not available on the market.

our business idea is building an electronic website which cares about marketing and shopping. This idea still not that popular specially in arab world ,this will give us the opportunity to occupy our place and be the premier electronic shopping and marketing website at least for some countries at the beginning.

column36:
Istebdaaâ€™ is based on both, the diminishing partnership model in the Islamic microfinance (a.k.a. Musharka Mutanaqessa) and the crowdfunding model. Therefore, it is based, from one hand, on  sharing profits and losses between Istedbaaâ€™s investment fund and the matched project. On another hand, it does not offer any returns on investment (ROI) except for the â€œcrowdâ€ who will get the product they crowdfunded . Of course the donors will not have any tangible ROI except the recognition of their sadaka. 

Therefore, our 3 main groups of clients (MSEs, product developers and the crowd) will only pay for results, and the fundamental upgrade in productivity and innovation due to Istebdaa" services.

Istebdaaâ€™ will invest in the â€œmatchedâ€ projects with a maximum amount of 30.000 EGP, and up to 50% of the total costs involved in the operation. In other words, after that Istebdaaâ€™ links the demand with the supply of innovation/ideas/product design it will invest in these latter as long as the total capital needed does not exceed 60.000 EGP.
The rest of the capital for each â€œmatchedâ€ projects will be shared between the firm, product designer and/or online community crowdunding (consumers or donors). The fund will go to the project itself as an independent legal entity, neither to the firm nor to the product developers solely. This will insure an additional mutual risk management, takaful. 

Every repayment of capital by the entrepreneur will diminish the total capital ratio for Istebdaaâ€™ in the project, as well as profit shares. Profits from each project are shared between stakeholders (including Istebdaaâ€™) and the firm gradually buys Istebdaaâ€™s shares in the project and share them with the designers till they both own 100% of the project within a predetermined timeline. As for the e-Sadaka and e-consumersâ€™ contributions, they will be considered as part of the MSEâ€™ shares. Any Sadaka issuer will be able to track the multiplication of his Sadaka in different projects.

The repayment period is dependent upon the pre-agreed period. It should be suitable till the development of the product (grace period till the commercialization).
An example: A Fanous Made by Egyptians
Workshops in Hussein and elsewhere, who are facing an aggressive Chinese competition through the last decade, need to innovate and upgrade the value chain for their fawanees by a cost-effective mean. Istebdaa" team will try to bring on the technical difficulties faced by those workshops and will look for solvers. 
Young innovators who might have funny and bright ideas for new forms of Fawanees. They can help workshops in adding some new functions in the products or a new production process for a better quality/price ratio. For instance, adding a new functionality to let it be useful even after the holy month ends.
As mentioned, our innovation system should be more demand-driven and based on the potential marketability and how to increase it. Therefore, Egyptian children must have a say and also contribute in the evolution of the Fanous. Throughout the portal, children and other internet-users will post ideas and suggestions for their Fanous. Through Crowdfunding, children"s parents will have the option to: (i) pay 10 LE as an e-Sadaka, (ii) pay 60 LE buy in advance the innovative fanous, and (iii) pay 120 LE and get a personalized fannous!
In addition, a contest could be organized in different regions of Egypt to let children draw the way they want their Fanous, and choosing among them the best designs.

Finally, the Fanous is the simplest example of how could we improve our economy by â€œinjectingâ€ more â€œknowledgeâ€ into it. The comeback of the Egyptian Fanous is only the beginning for a brighter future of our economy.
column51:
The Arab region is witnessing historical moments of change and hope; these youth-led movements are a clear illustration of what the synergy between youth and knowledge could do, from the one hand. Meanwhile, it has shown what societal risks can unemployment and hopelessness provoke. 
The current political change in Egypt would surely have many economic implications. The main economic challenges are, among others: (1) Fighting skilled youth unemployment , (2) Increasing the Egyptian workforce productivity  and (2) Upgrading the value-added and the marketability of the Egyptian products .
This needs an intermediation framework that matches the local societal needs, local knowledge with local and/or international markets. The main problem that is preventing any these factors from being matched was (1) the financial burden and more specifically the refusal of commercial banks to support such initiatives without any collateral, (2) the unclear perception of the innovative ideas demand & supply.

Our system takes some advantages over the competitors:
1. Efficiency: error is about 2-3 micrometer over manual plaster frames because of the hand-made errors and the normalization shrinkage factor of approximately 2-3 millimeter, less production cost in terms of money and time

2. It enables our customers using our system without buying expensive devices as our direct competitors through a prepaid web service (for getting the input medical images files and processing the 3D modeling) and delivery service (for the printed models) equivalent to our system.

3. We enable our customer integrating their iProducts (iPhone, iPad) and their Android to facilitate their interfacing our system and our services by developing iOS and Android clients.

A)FIRST TEAM MEMBER.
(RESEARCH,DEVELOPMENT AND TRAINING MANAGER)

-Research and provide background information to support community development; conduct forums/workshop in response to current issues and emerging trends impacting on the local and global trade/economies.

-Identify opportunities to collaborate with other organizations on research projects

-Research and review on quality and affordable entrepreneurship training materials.

-Research,review and identify areas of need for business start-ups; by exploring currents and emerging issues.

-Training the Qatar community on the need for business start-ups(Small Micro enterprises-SME).

-Empowering,motivating and creating awareness to the Qatar community on local and global business trends.

-Together with other staff, to develop written and verbal surveys,questionnaires, issue papers and other research tools on entrepreneurship and community development.

-Prepare articles for newsletter;information sheets, updates,website and other relevant publications.


B)SECOND TEAM MEMBER.
(HUMAN RESOURCE AND ADMINISTRATION OFFICER)

-Provide support to supervisors and staff to develop the skills and capabilities of staff.
-Coordinate staff recruitment and selection process in order to ensure a timely organized and comprehensive procedures is used to hire staff.
-Identify training and development opportunities.
-Monitor staff performance and attendance activities.


C)THIRD TEAM MEMBER.
(FINANCE AND OPERATIONS OFFICER)

-Administer and monitor the financial system in order to ensure that finances are maintained and budgeted in an accurate and timely manner.
-Maintain the accurate payable and accounts receivable systems in order to ensure complete and accurate records of all monies. 
-Administer employee files and records in order to ensure accurate payment of benefits and allowances.
-Provide efficient and effective financial etiquette for management.

column25:
Sherif Ali is in charge of the design and development of Amakena. He has huge experience in building large scalable web and portal solutions. He has previous experience in developing and running on-line stores.

Sherif Sabry is in guy behind the Amakena recommendation engine, one of the most important features of Amakena.com which helps users get recommendations based on their taste, their friends" and the public.

Ahmed Badr is a Wharton MBA and a management consultant at Bain and Company. He is in charge of the business and financial aspects of the project.
column27:
Amakena uniquely uses the social aspects of the web to help users with their buying decisions.

Amakena"s simplistic design helps users work it in an intuitive way which minimizes it"s learning curve. The site adapts according to usage, categories are rearranged based on user preferences and category access frequency.

Amakena is an open platform, meaning users can add an interest category (e.g. Rare Coin collections) and invite people to join these categories. When a category gets enough activity to be considered "popular", it is enabled as one of the main categories of the site.

Amakena integrates with existing social networking sites such as Facebook, Twitter and Google allowing users to use their existing identity on Amakena.
column43:
The most important factor for retailers is "how to reach their target demographic in volume". This is the main factor that affects their choice of location, marketing , expansion, etc. While some retailers have on-line stores, most of them are failing to utilize this channel, this is mainly because most retailers fail to realize that these types of Websites require constant marketing to drive growth and it can be as expensive as opening a brick and a mortar store.

Amakena makes use of the viral growth that characterizes social network sites and presents retailers and business owners with a great channel to reach their target demographics.

Retailers would simply catalog their products to create a virtual store called an â€œAStoreâ€. Each time a customer chooses to buy items from Amakena, AStores that contain these items are listed for the user to choose from. 

Amakena handles all logistical issues such as payment methods, shipment, etc. and creates a care free environment for the retailers to benefit from.
column51:
With too many options on hand, how do people decide on which new places to try, which books to read, TV series to watch, Music to listen to, etc? We have conducted a survey on 375 people, in the 18 - 44 age group that shows that people usually rely on their friends, people who share the same taste, expert reviews and the public opinion (e.g. Best Sellers, Box Office, etc.) as a big factor of their decision making process.

Amakena is a social cataloging website that provides users with an easy way to organize and share their favourite interests like books, movies, TV series and music among others with their friends, write reviews, share ratings, get recommendations based on their personal preferences, meet others with similar taste, buy their favorite items and get them delivered in the comfort of their homes.
