Our competitors are one factory in Lebanon and another one in KSA; they are exporting similar machines to Egypt. Also the regular system in all the bakeries in Egypt. Our competitive advantages: we are the first to develop a 100% automated bakery machine in Egypt; our machine will produce higher quality bread in much less time with lower cost. Also, a strong security system will be in the machine to prevent stealing the subsidized flour.
Indirect Competitors: Ovens" owners
column30:
We decided to do this project to solve one of the biggest crisis in Egypt, the bread crisis.

 

 

A lot of problems created the bread crisis in Egypt.

1- Stealing the subsidized flour by bakeries

2-The low quality, weight of the bread and it have no standards specifications

3-There is a lot of wasted flour in the baking process

4- There is a lot of people are taking bread more than they deserve, others take less than they deserve

5- Fuel is now decreasing
column33: Our idea simply is to make the subsidized bread industry in Egypt 100% automated, that will help us to ensure delivering the support to citizens with best quality and less time.
column40: We are now starting up our project. In one year, we will win 1st place in MIE and I2P. After that we will increase our sponsor list, and we will have our own factory. Then, we will start making our production line. In 3 years, we will increase the man power in our factory and start selling our product. In 5 years, we will have good distribution channels all over Egypt.
column51:
Our idea simply is to make the subsidized bread industry in Egypt 100% automated, that will help us to ensure delivering the support to citizens with best quality and less time.

 

But how will we do that ?!

 

We will manufacture a 100% automated bakery machine that will do the whole process of baking. We will put flour in it and wait for loaves at the other side.

 

We will make a 24/7 internet connection between the machine and the ministry of supply. The machine will record the amount of raw flour inside it and number of loaves produced. These recorded data will be sent to the ministry of supply daily. That will ensure an excellent supervision from the ministry of supply on the baker.

 

We will make the whole process automated. The machine will produce bread with its standards specifications which ensures best quality. That will save a lot of wasted raw materials in the manual industry.

 

We will make a database inside the machine which will have the data of the citizens in the neighborhood. That will help to let everyone get the deserved number of loaves daily, no more no less.

 

By making this machine, we are introducing a new way to solve one of the major crises prevailed in Egypt so far. We seek to have a national project which will help the people who suffered too much.

 

Not only that, we are seeking to develop our project in the future. We will add a renewable-energy source to make the machine work with its best efficiency.

 

Making the subsidized bread industry in Egypt 100% automated is not easy, but we dream to see â€œMade in Egyptâ€ on an Egyptian product. It will be our main motivation in this project.

column5: Data networks Team leader for a mobile operator
column17: B.Sc in electrical engineering (2002) , Masters of Business Administration ( 2008)
column19: 10 years experience in the design and implementation of IT solutions
column30:
Bawwaba offerings will contribute positively to the economic & social development in many ways:
- Provide financial access to the unbanked population.
- Easy and fast movement of money which will result in better productivity
- Boost the e-commerce business by providing a secure and convenient method of online payment.
- Provide the government with efficient ways to distribute subsidies (G2P)
column33:
The combination of high mobile penetration rate (close to 100%) and the limited access to financial services for most of the population (90% of adults are unbanked) presents a considerable opportunity for mobile money space. On the other hand, mobile operators are currently investing to build their mobile money infrastructure.

 To leverage this emerging mobile money ecosystem , Bawwaba will act as an intermediary offering innovative services such as Bill payments (C2B) , Bulk payments (B2C) , m-ticketing, etc..
column51:
Bawwaba will be a Mobile Payment gateway enabling merchants and online e-commerce websites to accept mobile money payments.  

On the other hand , Bawwaba will provide end customers with a simple , secure , and convenient method of payment using their m-wallet.

column23: Help the Environment, Help the Needy
column51: the idea is to make machines where people will have to put used water and/or coke bottles in, and they will either choose between getting money for it or donate that amount of money (can be 2 MAD or 3 MAD) to an association that will distribute it later to poor people!

column25:
Ahmed Al Farkh - Nawwer CEO
I will be the Chief Enlightenment Officer, overlooking company strategy, financials, accounting. i am skilled at public speaking and creating marketing campaigns. i am also skilled at creating relationships with key partners for the business. 

i have completed my Bachelor"s degree in Business Administration (Concentrations in Marketing and Management) from the American University of Sharjah. i was on the Chancellor"s List (GPA above 3.5) in my final year in the business school, which included my major marketing and management courses.

My last work experience has been at Namshi.com in the Offline Marketing team, where i have learned a lot about what to do and not to do to create a successful online startup. My responsibilities consisted mainly of creating partnerships with key companies and carrying out the campaigns that would create awareness about the brand and generate sales.

Previous to that i worked at the international management consulting firm Oliver Wyman as a Case Team Assistant (CTA) and before that i worked as a Marketing Intern at Zain (Bahrain) and as a Research Analyst at Delta Partners. 


Yasir El Nimr - Nawwer CMO
Known to be self-driven, to the point, and having a bird"s-eye view on most topics, I have graduated from the American University of Sharjah in 2010 with a Bachelors of Science in Computer Engineering. Last year, I have started my MBA as a part-time student at the University of Wollongong Dubai.

This week, I have quieted my job at GBM (IBM GMSR) as the Software Support Specialist to dedicate myself to Nawwer. At which I have managed a pipeline of software support renewal contracts worth $6M (2012) for top tier customers in 6 branches. Despite my quota of $4M, I have managed to surpass it by more than 50%. Additionally, my achievements are merely double the sales of year 2011. Being the contact point between IBM TSS team, and GBM ITS branch managers and account managers have made me attain management, negotiation, and problem solving skills.

During my university life, I was an adrenaline pumping student. Being a board member at the Computer club, I was responsible for media and public relations in organizing our trips, seminars, and competitions. Bringing in speakers from blue chip companies such as Microsoft and Nvidia was one of our successes. I have interned at the DIFC as a web designer and mentored at GBMâ€™s networking department. Additionally, I have freelanced as a graphic designer for Interactive Group to design posters, banners and invitations for a corporate event. 

As the Chief Marketing Officer at Nawwer, I will be responsible for the online/offline marketing. I will build on my design, PR, and marketing skills to attain website hits, build partnerships, and achieve customer satisfaction. 


Munzir Suliman - Nawwer CTO
I Grew up watching computers and other electronic parts scattered all over the house, raised in an environment where "possible" was up to the effort i put to what i want to achieve.

I always believed that everything in life, including science consists of symbols that identify and rule the laws to govern them. Thus i managed to teach myself MS Office and basic electronics and computer maintenance at the age of 13 and through such definition i gained most of what i know today . 

I don"t believe in titles where a person defines the knowledge he or she claims to have in mind based on some un-passionate compulsory readings. I believe in practices, passion, experiences and efforts to foster creativity and innovation in order to move forward. I have worked as a call center agent in a marketing research company known as TNS where I"ve acquired the required knowledge to move to BRIDGESTONE alserkal as a call center agent and there i got promoted in less than 5 months to become a shop manager and to be selected as the best in the year 2009. During that job I"ve managed to not only meet monthly sales targets, but also to influence technicians to become shop in-charges then shop managers. i"ve taken night classes to obtain an advanced diploma in marketing from a branch based in Dubai of an Australian college named Cambridge Collage International. i have also obtained a statement of accomplishment in databases through an online course offered by Stanford University USA.

I"ve managed to establish relations with Sharjah"s airport free zone through a marketing campaign conducted with a declared purpose of raising awareness for safety while the undeclared reason was to promote the company"s services. This plan has been replicated and reused with Sharjah"s government as well, as a result of the success with the first campaign. In the early days of 2010 got Rewarded with a promotion to join the marketing department as a Retail Marketing Executive. Seeking a better future i started working as a freelancer developing websites "mainly" in my brother"s company DOXYTERAA digital solutions and ever since i have been working as a freelancer looking to find the right cause that would make a difference, something that i would wake up every day happily to work on. This have been found in NAWWER.

Here is a video that best describes us as a team.  http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2a_8Ch6DfIs
column27: Our initial pilot stage will be undergone at the UAE. Our first expansion stage will include countries from the Middle East. We are also considering including popular international destinations for education in countries such as the US, UK, Canada, and Australia.
column29:
Direct Competition:
- Student recruitment agencies: These companies go to schools, universities, and educational exhibitions and conferences to recruit students into applying to their sponsored universities.
- edarabia.com: Provides Information, news, and reviews of education and educational institutions in the Arab region.
- noodle.org: Offers several online free services, including an education search - Targeting US.
- unifrog.org: A tool which helps students choose the best universities for them in the UK.
- ucas.ac.uk: Manages applications to higher education courses (majors) in the UK. 
- uni-assist.de: A uniform application service for international undergrad and graduate students, with 128 universities across Germany currently in their database.
- collegeboard.org: Global US-based non-profit organization, offering services under three main categories: College Readiness, College Connection and Success, Advocacy and Research. Their "BigFuture" is a college search tool.
- aaet.com.au: An independent, offline, and free of charge service to enroll international students in Australian educational institutions. 
- commonapp.org: an admissions platform for students wanting to apply to selected universities (mainly in the US)
- idp.com: an offline placement and support service institute that processes more than 25,000 international studentsâ€™ applications to study in the UK, Australia, US, Canada, or New Zealand. In addition to student placement, IDP provides counseling, visa assistance, and English language training for students. 

Indirect Competition:
- Counsellors: They offer personalized, free advice, but many are unreliable or unavailable in schools.
- Search engines: They can pose as indirect competitors at the start but prove to be powerful allies later on
column30: Our vision is to inspire the world for a better education. We are on a social mission of guiding students to the educational path that best suits their interests and strength.
column32:
Our licence and office costs are already covered by an incubation for 1 year that we have won during Startup Weekend Sharjah 2012 competition (2nd place). In addition, we are winners of the 4th place in Startup Weekend Dubai 2012 with a cash money of Dh10,000.

The $50,000 will be well spent on our pilot and expansion stages. Online/offline marketing, university/school visits, graphic designing, and social media are some of the considered spending schemes.

We are looking forward to continue our progress as we are all fully dedicated to our startup to make things happen.
column33:
When students are about to graduate from high school, many of them find themselves lost and confused. They have to make critical life-changing decisions, as they are conflicted with so many different choices of universities and majors. 

Not only that, they have to face pressure from their parents, friends, and communities when deciding what the best options for them are; and most of the time they don"t even have the slightest clue, which makes the experience even more distressing!

People at later stages in life face a similar dilemma when going into post graduate studies.

Universities also face issues when it comes to students applying to them. They find it difficult to recruit the right caliber of students to their programs. When students join, there is a high dropout rate among students not enrolled in the optimal field of choice. Also, the application process in most universities is paper-based and rigid, hence utilizing human, time, and capital resources in an ineffective and inefficient way.
column40: Our online business can easily expand adding in universities to our database and communicating our message to countries with large population of students. International destinations when added to our database will guarantee us scale even faster as to us not needing to update our database, but initiate in communicating our services to more countries.
column43:
Our main revenue stream is through university subscriptions to our service. In order to be listed as a university with the application feature universities pay us an annual subscription.

A secondary revenue stream is through student applications. Students will pay us a premium to apply through our portal online.

Additional revenue streams will be introduced from value-added services for students looking for the right major.

Of course, based on the feedback we get from the market, we will adapt and pivot accordingly.
column50: We have initiated preliminary discussions with students to understand their needs and wants. During our alpha (offline) stage of our website, we have planned to get a target number of students feedback on our website and pivot if required for a better strategy to get better results for students.
column51: Nawwer provides services that enable students to find the right university and major which is suitable for their particular needs and wants.

column27:
Our business is targeting Arab speaking countries.
And our customers will include all online users, and all companies interested in online marketing with an added value on health awareness.
column29:
Actually we don"t have direct competitors as the idea is a brand new one. But for sure we have competitors indirectly, those competitors are online websites providing health awareness messages and health advice, and those are around 3 competitors in middle east.
Other competitors are companies providing online marketing services, those companies are a lot, and we are actually different from them as we provide an online marketing using health awareness and by online subscribers which is effective, low cost and of an added value.
column30:
Our idea will have a very good impact on our community. The most important benefit that we will act as tool for health care awareness which will really affect the health of our people. Also, people will use our portal to spread health awareness messages, so they will work with us on different initiatives and have a role in changing their communities, which for sure will increase their sense of motivation to work in helping their community.
Our portal will provide a great working opportunity for youth, they can work at home as marketeers, and beside that they are a real change makers. Another benefit, is that we provide a good example of the usage of internet as a work tool not for entertainment, which is a very bad misconception in our Arabic countries.
column32: We will use this money to initiate our business, we need this money to work on technical development of the idea which is the core element to initiate our business.
column33:
Our idea will work to solve two main problems. First one is the great lack in health care awareness in our Arab world. The second one is the corporate social responsibility which is not used effectively to make a a change in our communities. Concerning health care awareness, the online arabic content is very poor, and the present content is not presented well. Also, till now there is not a good tool for spread of health awareness messages even after the era of social media. Our portal will provide health awareness in a very attractive way, using creative videos, games, info graphics which are produced by specialists in such field, also using our portal system, the awareness message will reach large number of people and make sure that the he or she received and understand the message and able to deliver it to another one. Subscribers in our portal will gain something in return, which is presented in points system which will be exchanged later on by money or any other benefits, all of this will make our message reach accurately to subscribers. 
The second problem we will solve is the need of companies to reach large number of customers easily, this will be provided with our online portal which will have large number of subscribers who will work as marketeers. Also, the companies will efficiently use their social responsibility as a marketing tool with great effect on their community, which is also a big problem we will solve.
column40:
Our business has a great ability to expand. Our portal will expand in two planes, as our customers present in two different planes. First one represents online subscribers, which itself is a powerful tool for sociability, people will have the desire to join our portal as they will gain benefit from it, they can gain money and also work as change makers.
The second plane, is that of companies and NGOs, our business will attract many companies to use our services which will provide a very effective marketing tool, low cost, with large target group, with great effect on community.
In general, the idea will be very attractive for both subscribers and companies as it will provide a good value for them.
column43:
The business will gain money as it will provide an online marketing service using health care awareness for companies and NGOs. They will pay for this service and other services we will provide like market analysis.
Also our health awareness products can be sold to interested media and companies which will be a good source for money
column50:
Concerning demand for our business idea, we did many informal contact with individuals, marketing specialists in pharmaceutical companies, workers in NGOs and entrepreneurs. Our contact was to ask about validity and applicability of the idea, either for subscribers or for companies and NGOs.
The feed back we got was that the idea is applicable and will provide a very good tool for users, and it will need high technical providers with powerful marketing.
column51: Our idea is that we would like to initiate an online portal which will work as a tool for health care awareness in a new and creative way. There is a great lack in Arabic health awareness web content, and most of present content is not presented in an attractive way. This is one side of the idea, the other side is that companies and NGOs must have a role in health care awareness as part of their social responsibility, they usually invest thousands of dollars for their marketing campaign with no benefit on the community they serve, we will provide companies a marketing tool by which they can reach their customers easily, and also affect their lives by spreading the health awareness message. Our online portal will have online subscribers, they will work with us to do a specific task, which will include spreading a message to others using social media, this message will contain two main contents, health awareness message and a marketing message for a specific company or NGO. Subscribers will have something in return according to their level of contribution in the tasks present on the portal. Subscribers will have a great role in their community development, and the companies also will have an easy, more effective and low cost marketing tool with an added value concerning their social responsibility.

column51: I did this project to produce cheap and clean energy for every place in Egypt that hasn"t electricity. This was a problem we had for too many years in Egypt but now this is no longer a problem. On the other hand we had many problems in Egypt and the world, but we considered these factors. We used the nature resources to help reducing the global warming, so we used the animals to produce energy because we have many animals according to our agricultural environment. We used the idea of the generator to transform the kinetic energy of the animals to electric energy. When I did my experiment it was difficult to success but we tried till it succeeded and we got electricity. We simply used the animal to move and turn gears. These gears are connected to the generator and the generator is connected to batteries that save the electricity.

column25: The business owner will be the manager of the business"s overall operations (i.e. myself, the applicant). Based on my experience I will be able to oversee the product creation, distribution channel set-up, supply management, and financial projections/management.
column27: The initial geographic target market will be the residents of Dubai in the UAE, though further geographies will be explored as the business becomes scaled. Focus will be made to expand into other arab countries as the business concept does not exist in the general MENA region, though is already present in other regions. The target customer base of the business will be persons aged 22-40 who prioritize nutritional food but do not have sufficient time to prepare meals.
column29:
There are no companies that have the same product concept in the target launch market. Though, one company provides fresh ingredients alongside printed recipes, though their demand proposition is under meal plans rather than single orders. They do appear to be dominant in the market and they do not market heavily.

There are several other companies internationally that provide customers with recipes plus fresh ingredients as a product concept.
column30:
Doorstep Cooking aims to provide healthy and wholesome nutrition through ethical and â€œgreenâ€ means.
All ingredients given to customers will be freshly sourced, and hence facilitating preservative-free food consumption amongst the local population.
Moreover, all products will be delivered in Eco-friendly packaging to raise consciousness about preserving the environment.
column32:
The prize money received from winning the compeition will go towards fitting the premises with preperation and storage tools, production of the cooking videos, building the website, and the brand creation.
Registration costs and initial operating costs will be covered by the business owner.
column33: Doorstep Cooking will provide its customers with an alternative to takeout meals and encourage them to eat â€œfreshâ€ by providing specific ingredient delivery and cooking tutorials, allowing for a more convenient home cooking experience. This will essentially address a growing local population trend towards requiring quick meals whilst protecting oneself from unknown additives typically found in food that is not prepared at home.
column40: After 1 year of operations, company management will evaluate the possibility of scaling Though Doorstep Cooking will initially be launched in one City, given that the primary order portal is made available online (the recipies and videos), the distrubtion can easily be scaled with local partnerships in other cities as the business grows. A franchise opportunity may also be modeled to facilitate this growth.
column43:
Doorstep cooking will charge customers per order submitted through the website for ingredients to prepare a particular recipie.
All menu items will be priced competitively with local take-out restaurants, accounting for a substitution for customers cooking the meals themselves.
The various recipes will be priced differently in correlation to the cost of the ingredients.
column50:
An online survery cover 100 participants was conducted covering various elements of the business such as preferences towards cooking at home, relevant of ingredients-availability to the liklinehood of cooking at home, home-meal cuisine preferences, and price preferences for meals.
All recipes will be tested for customer likeability in a focus group prior to the business launch.
column51:
Doorstep Cookingâ€™s offering is to deliver to customers the ingredients required to cook a meal at home. 
A variety of recipes will be listed on the website as videos, offering various cuisine types, which customers can choose from.
For each meal order, the exact required ingredients, based on the number of servings requested, will be packaged and delivered to customersâ€™ address.
The customers will then follow the videos, which will demonstrate how to prepare the selected meal.

column30:
Driven by social impact, Pi Slice empowers micro-entrepreneurs, who are otherwise excluded from access to credit by formal banking institutions, to start and grow businesses, engage in income-generating activities, and thereby transform their own lives as well as those of others by becoming job creators rather than job seekers. By giving a small online loan, a lender can provide aspiring micro-entrepreneurs with a life-altering opportunity to overcome poverty, enter the formal economy, and proliferate available employment opportunities, thus accelerating development. This would not only enable microfinance institutions (MFIs) to build a sustainable future for the industry, but also help shape the regionâ€™s future economies, communities, and competitiveness.  
In the regionâ€™s development process, the individuals & private sector is now presented with an unparalleled CSR channel to unlock the abilities of millions of unemployed youths, activate human capital in the labor force, and solve economic crises, hence actively contribute to the sustainable development of the MENA region. Today, Pi Slice unveils its MENA portal for individual and corporate investors, opening doors to a brighter future.
column32: 1.3 Million Dollars in Funding
column40:
Pi Slice will achieve its sales targets through a 2-pronged approach:  digital marketing and direct sales. 
Digital Marketing: Pi Slice will use a sophisticated digital marketing strategy which it has developed including social media (Facebook, Twitter), Google ads, PR & media presence, blog & microshows to reach as much as possible Arab internet users. Firstly, it will use SEO and online lead generation techniques to drive potential Lenders to its website. Secondly, it will launch an online marketing campaign on leading regional portals to attract traffic of potential Lenders. This will incorporate a social networking strategy on sites such as LinkedIn, Twitter, Branchout, Facebook targeting professionals, in addition to placing strategic ads on websites that are business & lifestyle orientated such as AME Info, Dubizzle, etc. Finally, it will send out targeted email campaigns to new and existing customers to increase its market share., Pi Slice has partnered up with Xische &Co. (one of its shareholders) to launch together an integrated digital media strategy.
Direct sales / Road show: The major market for Pi Slice will be corporate Lenders through their CSR programs. To attract corporations, Pi Slice will have a dedicated direct sales team to go and build close professional ties with leading companies. Through its business networks as well as attending CSR related events, Pi Slice will secure Lenders and corporate sponsorships.

Once integrated, they undergo a rigorous monitoring process assessing ongoing key risks, country risk with monthly financial reports & annual due diligence report
column51: Pi Slice is a social web based platform â€“ developed in partnership with MicroWorld from the  PlanetFinance Group - promoting social awareness and change. Its framework is a unique connecting system that links individuals and companies wishing to provide finance to MENA based MFIâ€™s, which in turn use the funds to provide micro-credit to their customers. Through this web based platform, motivated individuals and companies can help MFIâ€™s in the MENA region to build a sustainable future for micro-entrepreneurs & a favorable ecosystem for macro development. MicroWorld.org, part of the PlaNet Finance Group, is a peer-to-peer platform that launched 18 months ago in France. It has a similar model to Pi Slice, channeling funds from individual lenders and large companies to MFIs around the world, albeit so far with low penetration in MENA and so far only offering non remunerated loans for individual lenders.
column52:

-	Strong Technology partner with Tier 1 technology partner
-	Strong Tier 1 MFIs partners
-	Strong Media partner with an integrated Media Strategy
-	Strong & diversified Board ensuring regional exposure and credibility
-	Strong and passionate team with an entrepreneurship story
-	First mover advantage
Opportunities:
-	A pioneer in bringing a unique CSR & social investment channels into Microfinance funding for MENA companies  & interested individuals 
-	An original tool very needed in the region in the light of last yearâ€™s events and with the growing need of funding  or support for MFIs since they play a major role in the future economy
Weaknesses:
-	New concept for the region with a need to educate the general crowd
-	As an online business, the unknown is how the crowd will react to us & at what stage of marketing
Threats:
-	Force majeure like war or political instability in a MENA country

column24: HSC started its activities in the north of Lebanon, since Tripoli is taking a leap of faith when it comes to technology. column29: Direct competitors :Similar home automation service providers ( i.e Dabbas, Ghazawi, Al Ahliya..) Indirect competitors: Providers of standard electrical and security systems (normal switches and outlets..) and single control components (keypad door locks, motion controlled lighting...)
column33: HSC is bringing hardware, software and electricity all together. With an automated system that you can manage from a tablet/ a phone or a remote control, you can run your house sitting on a couch or being miles away.The interface is user-friendly for all backgrounds.A system that is cost-effective (1/5 of the original price) since HSC has its own designed hardware and software, which makes it easily customizable according to clients needs. If you have a 90 m2 or a 500 m2 mansion, our solution can turn a house into a cozy home with a click. Who wouldn"t dream of that? HSC is turning all electricity outlets into low voltage switches, which provides the safety for your loved ones. In addition, your personal "house" assistant will be there for you to check all your electricity consumption when you"re at a distance, you are always in control !
column51: Home security and control provides not only a home automation system for households but a service that enables them to have a luxurious lifestyle with a low budget. HSC manages your house whether curtains, electricity, heating system, doors and appliances through an application (web/mobile) to keep you in control  even if you are miles away.With a click , you"re providing your family with security and you are saving energy.

column30:
ThreatForge offer to its members a one-stop platform for security incident response which enables them to have a high and quick support from other incident handler members (e.g. CERT, CSIRT  ...) for resolving their security issues, in addition , ThreatForge enables the cooperation and the interactivity between the members in solving instantly the security incidents and managing the global security outbreaks.

One the other side, ThreatForge shares the knowledge and the experiences of the members within security incident handling and communicates all new security alerts, security bulletins, security feeds, emerging threats and attacks trends... This maximizes the security awareness and offers an in-depth knowledge in cyber security.

The project can offer an important number of employment positions for talents in cyber security, development, and marketing. In addition, it will generate benefits for the independent security researchers and the Whitehat security professionals members by enabling them to communicate their security researches and vulnerabilities discovered directly to the appropriate organizations
column32: Such ammount will enable us to complete our protoype and go to gather customers feedbacks and rebuild the platform and then starting our marketing strategy to make a professional expansion.
column33:
After the outcrop of the cyber hacktivists attacks such as Anonymous attacks and the other kind of social and targeted attacks and with the emersion of sophisticated and advanced threats, we realized how is important and primordial to have collaboration workplace which gather all the efforts in the cyber space to defend the assets and struggle against the emerging threats and help sharing experiences, advisories and trends of all kind of cyber threats: attacks, thefts, malwares.. ThreatForge is a unique project of its kind on a global scale which aims to democratize the incident handling and incident management tasks.

ThreatForge use smart and accurate processes and workflows to make possible to facilitate and automatize the elongated and complex processes of incident analysis and response, in addition it rounds up all the cyber space stakeholders which maximize the collaboration and the sharing and permit any platformâ€™s member to gather the experiences, informations and help from the other members.

Any ThreatForgeâ€™s member will have a unique and fully customized security services focusing on Threat Intelligence, Incident Handling, Security Dashboards, Security Alerts Aggregation, Forensics & Investigation, etc... where he can participate to the incident management lifecycle , in addition he will have access to an in-depth threat intelligence dashboard where he will build an extreme threat awareness knowledge ; security alerts , attacks trends , reputation database , real attacks map etc ..
column40: The idea of ThreaForge is already based on a globale scale thinking
column43:
The pricing approach will be based on annual subscription for corporate and organization users and free for individuals and communities.

The annual subscription fees will be from USD 1000 to USD 3000 , a special prices will be given to partners.
column51: ThreatForge is a web-based Security Incident Response and Management Platform which gathers all the stakeholders within the cyber space: CERT/CSIRT, Entreprises, Software Vendors, Datacenters, Antivirus & IDS/IPS Vendors, Internet Users, Open Source Communities, Universities, and Security Researchers etc... The concept of ThreatForge is based on global scale cooperation and collaboration within Incident Response and Handling, in addition, all platform users will have a package of customized and cost-effective threat intelligence services which are suitable to their roles and needs within the cyber space security movement.
